1 A concurrent resolution honoring the police and first responders of Fargo, North Dakota.
2 WHEREAS, on July 14, 2023, Fargo police officers and first responders courageously
3 responded to a tragic shooting incident that claimed a precious life and endangered public
4 safety; and
5 WHEREAS, Officers Andrew Dotas and Tyler Hawes, along with civilian Karlee Koswick,
6 were injured during this incident, demonstrating bravery under extreme circumstances; and
7 WHEREAS, Sergeant Zach Robinson, with skill and disciplined focus while under the most
8 difficult of circumstances, exercised amazing heroism in neutralizing the threat posed to the
9 Fargo community; and
10 WHEREAS, the swift actions of first responders prevented further loss of life and ensured
11 public safety during this critical event; and
12 WHEREAS, Officer Jake Wallin of the Fargo Police Department made the ultimate sacrifice
13 in the line of duty while protecting his community;
14 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
15 NORTH DAKOTA, THE SENATE CONCURRING THEREIN:
16 That the Sixty-ninth Legislative Assembly honors Officer Jake Wallin for his heroism and
17 extends heartfelt condolences to his family, friends, and colleagues; commends Officer Andrew
18 Dotas, Officer Tyler Hawes, and Sergeant Zach Robinson, for their bravery and resilience in the
19 face of danger; expresses sincerest gratitude to our nurses, doctors, and all other first
20 responders for their dedication to serving and protecting the Fargo community; and encourages
21 continued support for law enforcement officers and first responders who risk their lives daily to
22 ensure public safety; and
23 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that the Secretary of State forward copies of this resolution
24 to the Fargo Police Department, Officer Andrew Dotas, Officer Tyler Hawes, Sergeant Zach
25 Robinson, Karlee Koswick, and the fiance and family of Officer Jake Wallin.
